text:
This hawker centre at Crescent Mall is only busy in the mornings, and more than half the stalls would close after 200pm.

Guan Seng Carrot Cake is an excellent breakfast choice while in the evenings, Hai Kee Teochew Cha Koay Teow is the highlight, be prepared though to queue for more than 1/2 hour for the CKT.
Nothing beats the Soon Huat coffee stall with their divine $2.30 breakfast set with bread, eggs and kopi! A truly rare nostalgic experience of old school coffee shops

One of the great many Unesco World Heritage Cultural Site that offers lots of genuine hawker foods.  Telok Blangah Crescent food centre and market.

There are wide variety of food stalls and competition from stalls holders.

We were there early and no issue parking and the food centre wasn't crowded.  When we were leaving, the car park was full and others waiting to park their cars.

Come here for lunch often. Love this stall's squid/pork balls soup with "white meetaibak" (just seasoning, pork lard, beansprout and spring onions). So comforting. Labrador nasi padang is really great to have as well.
Superb prata with the gravy fish curry or dalcha so nice.Mee goreng,away towards goreng its a must try....The drink stall is a wow with long queue but worth it.Hot beverage is nice.
